Cell[TextData[{
 "Here, ",
 StyleBox["f1", "CodeText"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["f2", "CodeText"],
 " correspond to features (genes). ",
 StyleBox["source1", "CodeText"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["source2", "CodeText"],
 " correspond to two reservoirs. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779945807610292*^9, 3.779945808466236*^9}, {
  3.779945873469968*^9, 3.779945947023708*^9}, {3.779946747956052*^9, 
  3.7799467487770767`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d0123a80-e183-44d5-bb7b-\
e84887f94cbc"],

Cell["\<\
In order to compare pairs of reservoirs, I suggest you proceed as follows:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779945957890603*^9, 
  3.779945999755192*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"992e693d-f1eb-4984-bc80-\
d2bffc6a9132"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Make sure you understand how the plot is made.", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946007111696*^9, 
  3.7799460204147587`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"881c6769-5cad-495d-849b-\
c01585d5be1f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Systematically compare the scatterplot for pairs of sources and pairs of \
genes. The comparison between sources in this case is not as clear as the \
comparison between species in the Iris flowers problem. However, we can \
extract some preliminary conclusions. ",
 StyleBox["Which sources do you think are more different from each other?",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " These are the ones that the classifier you will train later should \
identify more accurately."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779946007111696*^9, 3.77994603175696*^9}, {
  3.7799460625194716`*^9, 3.7799460707511406`*^9}, {3.7799461589598846`*^9, 
  3.7799461628298306`*^9}, {3.7799464338644753`*^9, 
  3.7799465796698017`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0e8dfa19-ae9f-4690-b49e-\
c494a01d91ec"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Task 9", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779802962449816*^9, 3.779802964633836*^9}, {
  3.779968871535158*^9, 
  3.779968873171789*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"10ac078c-1b99-4c78-8fc5-\
9c1db67aadd5"],

Cell["\<\
In order to further analyse the data and try to confirm some of your \
conclusions in the previous task, plot a scatter plot matrix. In order to \
reduce the complexity of the scatter plot matrix, you may want to plot a \
reduced number of features (genes) at once.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779802974179901*^9, 3.779803067589616*^9}, 
   3.7798987651026793`*^9, {3.7799474117375174`*^9, 3.779947507811039*^9}, {
   3.77994812469623*^9, 3.7799482042470427`*^9}, {3.814100704510593*^9, 
   3.8141007361120777`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3ce58208-5e92-4983-99fd-\
809452e5ed70"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Task 10", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799482462858205`*^9, 3.779948248895197*^9}, {
  3.779968880673505*^9, 
  3.7799688843632774`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4ef92538-0773-4973-a373-\
a70077634b24"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To train a classifier with the source isolates and test its performance, \
you will need to define training and test datasets from the ",
 StyleBox["dataSources", "CodeText"],
 " list.\n\nIn ",
 StyleBox["dataSources", "CodeText"],
 ", there are some isolates that are identical (i.e. they share the same \
features). See, for instance the first 10 elements of the ",
 StyleBox["Tally", "CodeText"],
 " counts in ",
 StyleBox["dataSources", "CodeText"],
 ":"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799492072884054`*^9, 3.7799493262181435`*^9}, {
  3.7799493680926995`*^9, 3.7799494158102093`*^9}, {3.7799527386973686`*^9, 
  3.7799527756229315`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"26dce777-91a2-4c77-a242-\
1e2a50131e69"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Take", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Tally", "[", "dataSources", "]"}], ",", "10"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799494580096917`*^9, 3.779949484445376*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[247]:=",ExpressionUUID->"0f0ab6dd-96fd-4b01-afa5-e25174596545"],

