Cell["\<\
For instance, there are 8 isolates from cattle with the genotype \
{Cattle,19,24,23,20,26,16,15}.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799528275310783`*^9, 
  3.779952867172845*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e23fb36b-af6e-4df6-9e3d-\
6342a833f259"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Due to the repeated genotypes, to define training and test datasets you \
should select element numbers in lists, i.e. it is not as simple as what was \
done for the Iris plant example. For instance, to select 75% of the isolates \
from ",
 StyleBox["dataSources", "CodeText"],
 " at random to define the training dataset, we proceed as follows:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799528726820216`*^9, 3.7799529061197634`*^9}, {
  3.7799530316945515`*^9, 3.779953102434248*^9}, {3.7799531734215527`*^9, 
  3.779953265945096*^9}, {3.8141864551112843`*^9, 
  3.814186481026319*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"788ff2f6-5225-4762-bc20-\
cc188d3e1879"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "First calculate the number of isolates corresponding to 75% of the total in \
",
 StyleBox["dataSources", "CodeText"],
 StyleBox[". Let us refer to this quantity as ", "Text"],
 StyleBox["ntrain.", "CodeText"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799532861160264`*^9, 3.7799533371472425`*^9}, {
  3.814186212422621*^9, 
  3.8141862238571463`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fd5771d3-839d-44f7-a610-\
409d3c570097"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Choose ",
 StyleBox["ntrain", "CodeText"],
 " indices from the set {1,2,...,Length[dataSources]} at random for the \
training data. Let us refer to the resulting set of indices as ",
 StyleBox["indexTraindata", "CodeText"],
 StyleBox[".",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779953430664605*^9, 3.7799535118663855`*^9}, {
  3.8141008306842017`*^9, 3.8141008488406076`*^9}, {3.8141862612337093`*^9, 
  3.814186280642109*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2a22680d-255d-4f47-a3c6-\
d85b81a68905"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Use the Complement function to define indices to be chosen from the \
original set to define the test dataset. Hint: This is the complement between \
a set of all the indices in ",
 StyleBox["dataSources", "CodeText"],
 " and in ",
 StyleBox["indesTraindata", "CodeText"],
 "."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779953566583828*^9, 3.77995359530083*^9}, {
  3.814186325441502*^9, 
  3.8141863820185833`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a16a9cdb-9ba7-4730-9610-\
6666e1766cee"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Check that the intersection between ",
 StyleBox["indexTraindata", "CodeText"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["indexTestdata", "CodeText"],
 " is null."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7799536117481823`*^9, 
  3.7799536368891134`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8a093d15-dd52-4855-92ab-\
2d67482e5f36"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Use the indices ",
 StyleBox["indexTraindata", "CodeText"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["indexTestdata", "CodeText"],
 " to define lists for training and testing from ",
 StyleBox["dataSources", "CodeText"],
 ". I will refer to these as ",
 StyleBox["traindata", "CodeText"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["testdata", "CodeText"],
 ", respectively."
}], "Item",
